   <text>
      <body>
         <lg>
            <l enjamb="no">Lady, Lady, I saw your face,</l>
            <l enjamb="no">Dark as night withholding a star.</l>
            <l enjamb="yes">The chisel fell, or it might have been</l>
            <l enjamb="no">You had borne so long the yoke of men.</l>
         </lg>

         <lg>
            <l enjamb="no">Lady, Lady, I saw your hands,</l>
            <l enjamb="no">Twisted, awry- like crumpled roots,</l>
            <l enjamb="no">Bleached poor white in a sudsy tub,</l>
            <l enjamb="no">Wrinkled and drawn from your rub-a-dub.</l>
         </lg>

         <lg>
            <l enjamb="no">Lady, Lady, I saw your heart,</l>
            <l enjamb="yes">And altared there in its darksome place</l>
            <l enjamb="no">Were the tongues of flame the ancients knew,</l>
            <l enjamb="no">Where the good God sits to spangle through.</l>
         </lg>

      </body>
